Currently passengers must disable its smartphones, tablets, and other devices, as soon as the door of the plane closes.
They should not restart them until the aircraft has reached an altitude of 10,000 feet and the captain did not give «good».
Passengers must turn off your device again, when the aircraft is reduced for planting, and to exclude them until the aircraft is on the ground.
In accordance with the new guidelines, airlines whose planes are adequately protected from electronic interference, it may allow passengers to use these devices during take-off, landing and taxiing, said the FAA.
Most new aircraft and other aircraft, modified so that the passengers could use Wi-Fi at high altitudes, is expected to meet these criteria.
Laura Глейдинг, President of the Association of professional flight attendants, welcomed these changes.
«After the new policy will be successfully implemented (and we're going to work closely with the carrier to achieve this), it will be a win-win situation,» said Глейдинг.
