New антиникотиновая vaccine may deprive the process of Smoking pleasure
Scientists have developed антиникотиновую vaccine, which could deprive the process of Smoking cigarettes pleasure.
One dose of vaccine could protect mice from nicotine addiction for life.
Further tests before the start of the trials, which will take several years, but the Professor Ronald Crystal of the medical College Уэйлл Cornell in new York said that the first results are encouraging.
«We hope this strategy for the use of the vaccine could finally help the millions of smokers who try to quit, having tried all the methods available on the market today, but found that their nicotine addiction is strong enough to overcome it with the help of these modern means,» said Professor at Cornell.
The new vaccine contains a harmless virus, which was designed to carry genetic information for the production of антиникотиновых antibodies.
Virus selectively infects liver cells, which then begin to produce a steady stream of antibodies.
Antibodies stalk any molecule of nicotine in the blood, neutralizing them before they reach the brain, preventing the obtaining of a smoker nicotine kick.
In tests vaccinated mice that later gave nicotine, continued their normal activity.
But mice that were not given the vaccine, «relax», and this is a sign that nicotine reaches their brain, say the researchers.
These experiments are described in the journal Science Translational Medicine.
Previous tobacco vaccine failed, because they contained antibodies.
To maintain a high level of antibodies, injections should have done so often that they were expensive and impractical.
But the cost of a new vaccine is likely to be much lower, because it turns the liver cells in the factories of antibodies.
Professor Crystal said that if future human vaccine was completely safe, it could be given to children before they have the desire to try a cigarette, preventing nicotine addiction.
But it is more likely that it will be used smokers to quit Smoking.
«They know that if they are to start Smoking again, will not give them this pleasure because of the nicotine vaccine, and it can help them to get rid of this habit,» he said.
British scientists said the results were interesting, but warned that more research is needed.
