The Agency "Rosbalt" has been deprived of the status of the media for swearing
October 31, the Moscow city court ruled to invalidate the license of the registration Agency "Rosbalt", - writes the "Ribbon".
The deprivation of the Agency the status of the media insisted Roskomnadzor for systematic and gross violations of the law on mass media.
In the course of the process was a very unfortunate precedent: the court considered it possible to close down the media, actually denying the publication of the right to put forward counter-arguments.
What is the "Rosbalt"
CJSC "Information Agency Rosbalt" was established in St. Petersburg in 2000.
In subsequent years, the Agency opened a second head office in Moscow and a number of regional offices.
Also the Agency has representative offices in the countries of the former USSR.
Since 2001, the "Rosbalt" was developed and functioned as a Federal information-analytical Agency.
By mid-2000s, the Agency included in the list of the most recognizable private online media in Russia.
The "Rosbalt" has always held a very specific niche: the core of the exclusive Agency publications were (and are still) notes referring to sources in law enforcement bodies.
Talk about the proximity of the edition to the security forces continued throughout the existence of the Agency.
Along with the fact that "Rosbalt" had an extensive base of sources in different departments, in favour of such assumptions spoke and that the head of the project there was Natalia Chaplin - wife of Victor Cherkesov.
The role of Чаплиной guide Росбалтом" unclear: most often it is called the "project Manager".
General Director of the Agency is Larisa Afonina, chief editor, Nikolai Ulyanov.
In the last time "Rosbalt" did not appear in the rankings of the Federal mass media - not for citation, nor on the audience.
In October, the Agency took 25th place in the rating of the sites attendance Russian media version LiveInternet.
According to the same LiveInternet, the average daily audience of the site rosbalt.ru about 150 thousand unique visitors (and up to 500 thousand views), monthly - about three million unique visitors.
Among the most popular materials for the last five months - notes about the helplessness of the Kremlin in relations with Ukraine, the death of the soloist of group "the King and the jester", the riots in the capital Бирюлеве.
The conflict of "Rosbalt" with Roscomnadzor began in July 2013, when the amendments to the media law, which prohibited the journalists foul language.
The office found a prohibited vocabulary two published on the Agency website videos ("Dzhigit from Krasnodar" and "Pussy Riot defiled oil derricks").
Further, the parties describe different.
Roskomnadzor on the basis of identified videos accused the "Rosbalt" in the gross and systematic violation of the law on mass media and addressed the court demanding to deprive the Agency of the license.
In "Росбалте argued that the claims office is unwarranted: first, rollers were not editorial materials, secondly, abusive words in them were masked, and, thirdly, right, after warning the videos were removed from the site.
Representatives of the Agency challenged the claims of Roscomnadzor arbitration court and when 22 October 2013 Moscow city court accepted a claim of Roscomnadzor, consideration of these complaints still continued.
However, already the 25th day of the magistrate judge issued a decision not in favor of "Rosbalt": chief editor Nikolai Ulyanov was found guilty of violating the administrative code and fined on 20 thousand roubles - on 10 thousand for each movie.
Obviously, it has predetermined the outcome of the hearing at the Moscow city court - if abandon the idea that the outcome could be a foregone conclusion even before.
on October 31 the court decided to annul the certificate of registration of "Rosbalt", effectively eliminating the Agency the status of the media.
Not to say that the "Rosbalt" in the course of this conflict remained alone.
The Agency was supported by the deputies of the state Duma (an application addressed to the head of Roskomnadzor Alexander Zharov 10 October signed by 26 deputies; the document was submitted on the initiative of the Communist party).
On the illegality of the closure of the periodical stated the head of the Union of journalists of Russia Vsevolod Bogdanov, Chairman of the Moscow Union of journalists Pavel Gusev, the head of the presidential human rights Council Mikhail Fedotov.
Moreover, according to Mr. Bogdanov, manual Roscomnadzor even gave him some assurance that the revocation of the license will not come.
Trial over "Росбалтом" revealed: under whose jurisdiction a bit safer mass media in Russia today is a big question.
